msg.storage.ui.segment-gran.title: What is Segment granularity?
msg.storage.ui.segment-gran.description:
The granularity to create segments at.

Druid data is stored in "datasources" and each datasource is partitioned by time.
Each time range is called a "chunk" (for example, a single month, if your datasource is partitioned by month).
Within a chunk, data is partitioned into one or more "segments". Each segment is a single file, typically comprising up to a few million rows of data.
msg.storage.th.query.gran.title: What is Query granularity?
msg.storage.th.query.gran.description: The minimum granularity able to query the results at and the granularity of the data inside the segment. E.g.'minute' means that data is aggregated at minute granularity. If there are collisions in the tuple (minute(timestamp), dimensions), then it will aggregate values together using the aggregators instead of storing individual rows.

msg.storage.ui.recommend.filter.descript: If you have a column that contains large amounts of data, loading the datasource can take a long time and cause a timeout error. Data manager can help you organize your dashboards or charts by registering columns with such errors as recommended filters. Dashboard administrators cannot remove suggested filters, and they are required to set filter values when configuring dashboards.
